**Kubernetes apply commands** 

kubectl apply -f mongo-secret.yaml
kubectl apply -f mongodb-depl.yaml
kubectl apply -f mongo-configmap.yaml 
kubectl apply -f mongoExp-depl.yaml 

**Kubernetes get commands; 
kubectl get pod
kubectl get pod --watch             // used to watch the status of pods in a Kubernetes cluster in real-time. When you run this command, it will display a continuously updating list of pods and their status, and it will automatically refresh as new pods are created or as existing pods change their status.
kubectl get pod -o wide
kubectl get service
kubectl get secret
kubectl get all | grep mongodb 

**Kubernetes debugging commands ** 
kubectl describe pod mongodb-deployment-xxxxxx
kubectl describe service mongodb-service
kubectl logs mongo-express-xxxxxx

** give a URL to external service in minikube ** 
minikube service mongo-express-service



